cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with video object segmentation, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a novel architecture for the same. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, specifically deep learning, for which cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of optimization techniques, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of video data, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a fast and efficient method, which could be relevant to robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category as well.
